description:
If I have a URI with an apostrophe in it, Virtuoso handles this just fine in SELECT, INSERT, etc. For example,
select <http://a'> where { }

returns the URI unchanged. Which is correct, since apostrophe is an allowed character in URIs (RFC 2396, section 2.3, production "mark").
However, if I do
construct { <http://a'> <http:/b> <http:/c> } where { }

then I get back http://a\u0027 which is doubly wrong. It's wrong because that's not the way to escape characters in URIs, and because this character shouldn't be escaped at all.
